LINE.Text: Traditional economics views humans as robotic machines who make calculated decisions based
on logic. In contrast, behavioural economics views humans as irrational and emotional beings
who are influenced by biases andexperience when making decisions. Traditional economics
is the theory; behavioural economics is the reality.
Decision making is a mixture of both system 1 and system 2 thinking - it can be considered as a continuum rather than a discrete choice between systems.
